<HEADLINE> Drug Pusher Arrested in Pakistan </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, September 2 (Xinhua) -- Pakistani Anti Narcotics
Force (ANF) in Quetta, capital of Balochistan province, arrested a
drug peddler named Abdul Karim Barkazai who was selling heroin to
addicts in the city on Saturday.
</P>
<P>
A total of 500 grams of heroin were recovered from his
possession, the Associated Press of Pakistan (APP) reported.
</P>
<P>
In another case, Frontier Corps troops in Balochistan province
seized 30 kilograms of hashish and 15 kilograms of heroin in an
area close to Pak-Iran border. No arrest was made so far. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
