<P>
BOGOTA -- Colombian Defense Minister Luis Fernando Ramirez said
Saturday that at least 50 guerrillas of the Revolutionary Armed
Forces of Colombia (FARC) have been killed in the fighting in the
western mountains of the Risaralda department.
</P>
<P>
A colonel and seven soldiers were killed in an ambush and in
the attack against the FARC, and seven more died early Saturday
when a military aircraft that was supporting the troops on the
ground crashed against a mountain. (Columbia-Rebels-Death)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
MOSCOW -- Russian President Vladimir Putin said Sunday that
Moscow recognizes the presence of territorial problem with Tokyo,
but will not transfer the Kuriles Islands to Japan.
</P>
<P>
Putin made the remarks in Russia's Far East city of Yuzhno-
Sakhalinsk on Sunday morning before leaving for Tokyo for a three-
day official visit, Russian media reported.
</P>
<P>
"Russia recognizes there is territorial problem between Russia
and Japan, but there is no question of turning over the Kuriles,"
he told reporters. (Russia-Japan-Kuriles)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
BELGRADE -- As many as 15 Serb prisoners escaped en mass from a
jail in the northern Kosovo city of Kosovska Mitrovica Saturday
night, the Yugoslav news agency Tanjug reported Sunday.
</P>
<P>
At about 9:00 p.m. local time Saturday, one Serb inmate
overpowered the guard while making a telephone call, took the keys
from him and opened the cells where other Serbs were kept, a
spokesman for the U.N. mission in Kosovo was quoted as saying by
the agency.
</P>
<P>
But two of them were caught later and a search for the other
escapees was under way, the spokesman said. (Kosovo-Serb-Prisoners)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
