<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Cacho Quits Olympics in Sydney </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>

<P>
MADRID, September 3 (Xinhua) -- Spain's 1500m Olympic champion
Fermin Cacho announced on Sunday that he would not compete at the
Sydney Olympic Games because he is suffering from tendinitis.
</P>
<P>
The Spaniard, who won silver in Atlanta four years ago, had
been struggling since he injured an Achilles tendon at a meet in
Padova on August 27, according to reports Sunday.
</P>
<P>
Cacho, 31, a two-time world outdoor silver medallist and
crowned European champion in 1994, ran through the pain barrier to
qualify for Sunday's 1500m national championships final but on
getting up on Sunday morning had to finally admit defeat, reports
said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
