<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 3 (Xinhua) -- The first Beijing
International Fruit Festival came to an end at the weekend with a
total transaction volume exceeding 13 million yuan (1.57 million U.
S. dollars).
</P>
<P>
More than 500 Chinese and overseas fruit traders brought 70
varieties of fruits to the five-day festival, according to an
organizing committee official.
</P>
<P>
Among the traded fruits, 70 percent were from overseas. As a
result, the wholesale prices of imported fruits on the Beijing
market in recent days were 20 percent lower than usual.
</P>
