<HEADLINE> Public Fete of Chinese Ancestor Staged in Tianshui </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LANZHOU, September 3 (Xinhua) -- Thousands of people from home
and abroad gathered today attending a ceremonious fete for Fuxi,
known as one of the first legendary ancestors of the Chinese
Nation, in Tianshui, northwest China's Gansu Province.
</P>
<P>
The ceremony was held in front of the Fuxi Temple, the biggest
temple for commemorating the ancestor in China.
</P>
<P>
Zhang Jinliang, mayor of Tianshui, read the funeral oration
expressing people's wish of restoring the glory of the ancient "
Silk Road" during China's efforts to develop the western region.
</P>
<P>
Tianshui, the birthplace of Fuxi, who is believed to be one of
those credited with introduction of hunting, farming and fishing
and of the Fuxi Culture, is generally considered the cradle of
Chinese civilization. 
</P>
