<HEADLINE> Rock Paintings Make Debut for Visitors </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
YINCHUAN, September 3 (Xinhua) -- A gallery of rock paintings
at Mount Helan in northwest China's Ningxia Hui Autonomous Region
was opened to visitors today.
</P>
<P>
And an international symposium on rock paintings was also held,
attracting more than 130 Chinese and foreign scholars.
</P>
<P>
Experts say that the tens of thousands of rock paintings carved
by nomads in northern China some 2,000 years ago at Mount Helan
are of great historic, artistic and scientific value, and Ningxia
will become a center of world rock painting research.
</P>
<P>
However, the tourist value of the rock paintings has long been
neglected. In order to better protect the paintings and attract
more visitors, Ningxia established an administration committee for
the rock paintings and built a new road leading up to the mountain.
</P>
<P>
Ningxia is also planning to set up a World Rock Painting Museum
at Mount Helan. 
</P>
</TEXT>
