<HEADLINE> International Yak Symposium Draws Experts Attention </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LHASA, September 3 (Xinhua) -- More than 200 Chinese and
overseas experts have flown to Lhasa, capital of southwest China'
Tibet Autonomous Region, to attend the 3rd International Symposium
on Yaks, which will open tomorrow.
</P>
<P>
During the six-day symposium, experts from a dozen of countries
and regions including Germany, France, England and the United
States will have academic exchanges on breeding, nutrition,
treatment of diseases and the environment of yaks.
</P>
<P>
Business and cooperation talks will also be held during the
symposium to promote the yak industry in Tibet.
</P>
<P>
There are about 14 million yaks in the world, living on high
and cold plateau, with 12 million in China's Qinghai-Tibet Plateau.
Meat, dairy and woolen products from yaks are popular on
international markets. 
