real danger to Australia who scored an overwhelming 95-53 win.
</P>
<P>
Six of the 12 teams who will play in the Sydney Olympics are
taking part in the tournament here. Yugoslavia (1-0), Canada (1-0)
and China (0-2) are in Group A while Australia (1-0), Italy (1-0)
and Angola (0-2) are in Group B. The winners of the two groups
will clash Wednesday in the final. 
