<HEADLINE> Spain Pounds Japan 99-58 at Friendly Series </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TOKYO, September 3 (Xinhua) -- European silver medallist Spain
overcame its sluggishness at first stage to rout Japan 99-58 in
the Dream Games Basketball friendly series at Yono on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
The jet-lagged visitors failed to concentrate well in the
beginning as the Japanese led 13-11 after the first five minutes.
</P>
<P>
Spain took time to get used to the Japanese style. In the end
Roberto Duenas and Alberto Angulo scored 14 points each, Juan
Carlos Navarro 13 points, while captain Alberto Herreros had 12
points.
</P>
<P>
Spain, who were drawn with Russia, Angola, Canada, Australia
and Yugoslavia in the Group B preliminary round in Sydney, will
challenge top favourites the United States Tuesday in the three-
nation series here. 
