<HEADLINE> 15 Serb Prisoners Escape From Kosovo Jail </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BELGRADE, September 3 (Xinhua) -- As many as 15 Serb prisoners
escaped en mass from a jail in the northern Kosovo city of
Kosovska Mitrovica Saturday night, the Yugoslav news agency Tanjug
reported Sunday.
</P>
<P>
At about 9:00 p.m. local time Saturday, one Serb inmate
overpowered the guard while making a telephone call, took the keys
from him and opened the cells where other Serbs were kept, a
spokesman for the U.N. mission in Kosovo was quoted as saying by
the agency.
</P>
<P>
But two of them were caught later and a search for the other
escapees was under way, the spokesman said.
</P>
<P>
The report said that many Serbs have been jailed without trial
for nearly one year and they often held demonstrations protesting
injustice against them. 
</P>
