<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Iranian President Leaves for U.N. Summit </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, September 3 (Xinhua) -- Iranian President Mohammad
Khatami left here on Sunday for New York to attend the U.N.
Millennium summit slated for September 6-8.
</P>
<P>
Foreign Minister Kamal Kharrazi and head of the president's
office Mohammad Ali Abtahi are among those accompanying Khatami in
his three-day visit to New York, the official Islamic Republic News
Agency reported.
</P>
<P>
During his visit, Khatami will meet with about 30 heads of state
and a group of Iranians residing in the United States.
</P>
<P>
He will also address the U.N. "Dialog Among Civilizations"
conference due to open on Tuesday. The conference will be held
under the aegis of Iran, the U.N. Educational, Scientific and
Cultural Organization and the U.N. Secretariat.
</P>
<P>
Presidents and prominent personalities from over 160 countries
will attend the millennium summit, which is the largest gathering
of world leaders in history.
</P>
<P>
The U.N. General Assembly adopted a resolution in November 1998
to name the year 2001 as the "Year of Dialog Among Civilizations,"
echoing Khatami's proposal to hold such a dialog among world
nations. 
</P>
</TEXT>
