<HEADLINE> India's Inflation Falls </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, September 3 (Xinhua) -- India's inflation rate fell
below the six percent level to stand at 5.73 percent during the
week ended August 19, an official release said here on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
The inflation rate fell to 5.73 percent from the level of 6.03
percent in the previous week mainly due to a decline in the prices
of non-food articles, said the release.
</P>
<P>
However, the rate was still much higher than that in the
corresponding week of last year, which was only 2.99 percent.
</P>
<P>
The wholesale price index for all commodities stood at 153.2
during the week ended August 19 as against 152.9 in the previous
week, showing a 0.2 percent rise, the release added. 
