political parties and 10 independent groups have handed in their
nomination lists by Saturday for the forthcoming general elections
scheduled on October 10, according to the Elections Commission.
</P>
<P>
Among those parties who have handed in their nomination papers,
the ruling People's Alliance (PA) has filed nominations in 13
districts, the main opposition United National Party (UNP) in 15
districts and the JVP, or People's Liberation Front, in two
districts.
</P>
<P>
In the districts in the north and east of the country where the
minority Tamils dominate, the leading Tamil parties including
Tamil United Liberation Front (TULF), People's Liberation
Organization of Tamil Eelam (PLOTE), and Tamil Eelam Liberation
Organization (TELO) and some independent groups handed in their
nomination papers on Friday. All leading Tamil parties including
the Eelam People's Democratic Party (EPDP) have handed in
nominations in the Wanni, Batticaloa and Trincomalee districts.
</P>
<P>
Nomination for the October general elections is due to be
closed on Monday. All 45 recognized political parties in Sri Lanka
are expected to contest the elections. The PA and UNP are the arch
rivals in the contest. There are altogether 22 electoral districts
in the island nation.  
</P>
