<HEADLINE> UAE Urged to Form Federal Tourism Body </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ABU DHABI, September 3 (Xinhua) -- A senior official of the
United Arab Emirates has recommended the setting up of a federal
tourism authority to promote the country as a tourist destination
worldwide, reported local media on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
Sheikh Tariq bin Faisal Al Qasimi, chairman of the Economic
Development Department, has stressed the importance of establishing
such a federal authority to further promote the image of the
country in the world, and to support the national economy by
boosting the local tourism industry.
</P>
<P>
Sheikh Tariq commented that setting up such an authority has
become a vital need since the tourism industry in the UAE is
growing day by day, saying "wherever you go in the world, you find
countries have their own national tourism ministries or
authorities. So there is no reason why we should not have the same
here in the UAE."
</P>
<P>
Furthermore, he said, it will support federal tourism
development and boost local tourism plans in each emirate as well.
</P>
<P>
The UAE has yet an unified authority in charge of the country's
tourism business, while the tourism is now operated by individual
emirates, facing many difficulties in building big infrastructure
projects in the field of tourism. 
</P>
</TEXT>
